genresAdvancedInfo.name: sanfona
genresAdvancedInfo.description: Sanfona is a type of Brazilian accordion music that originated in the northeast region of the country. It is characterized by its fast-paced rhythms, lively melodies, and the use of the sanfona accordion as the lead instrument. The music is often associated with traditional Brazilian folk culture and is commonly played at festivals and celebrations.
